Welcome to the Corporate Casket, a semiweekly series where bad businesses go to die. We will discuss any and everything from bad charities, terrible CEOs, and businesses that have a lot to hide. 

Everyone knows to expect delays and traveling headaches during the holiday season. It’s just what happens when thousands of people fly at the exact same time all across the world at the time of the year when the weather is an especially terrifying factor. Unfortunately, some travelers had a few more issues this past holiday season than they bargained for if they were traveling with one particular airline: Southwest. As thousands of flights were canceled, and stories of people sleeping in airports began sweeping across the news stream everyone was left wondering; what is going on here? What happened to Southwest in 2022?
